  • All Classes Interface Summary Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Ball
    This is the ball class THe ball is a moving object and it is collidable.
    Collidable  
    CollisionEvent  
    CollisionManager  
    Convayor
    The conveyor moves objects that hit it depending on what is set by in firstwindow determines what direction the conveyor will go.
    Crusher
    The crusher will turn any object with the property crushable==true to the color magenta This crusable status is set by scanner1.
    CustomPanel
    Custom panel is where all the lists of everything that is on the panel is stored.
    DisposalArea
    The disposal extends of polygon so it behaves as a polygon The difference is if that any moving object hits it it will destroy it.
    FirstWindow
    This is main where the everything get initialized.
    MovingObject  
    MovingObjectAnimator  
    PolyGon
    The polygon class is what all static objects in my simulation are made of The special functionality of this class is that it can dynamically draw a boundary box just from the coordinates specified from FirstWindow.
    Scanner
    The scanner is a polygon with special properties It is Collidable and will set crushable to true if a blue square hits it It will require two lists of ints to create its outline.
    Square
    The square is a class that is a moving and collidable object This class is similar to the ball class although it has extra properties like crushable and trapdoorStatus
    TrapDoor
    The trapdoor class extends polygon as it is a static shape and it is a collidable When scanned square (scanned by the trapdoor scanner) has a trapdoor status of true it will allow the square to pass through, instead of going down the conveyor as it is technically a conveyor.
    TrapDoorScanner
    The trap door scanner scans for magenta squares and if it finds one it will set its trapdoor status to true The trap door will read this status This class extends polygon as it is a static shape and it is also a collidable
